; 
<figureCitation id="C08762D2FF9FFF99C63BF9BCDC33F9B1" box="[770,851,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[264,383,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[276,1314,341,1696]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,299,1712]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Dorsal habitus of Meligethes epeirosi n. sp. (♂ paratype from Greece, Katara Pass, Fig. 1), of M. subaeneus Sturm (♂ specimen from Italy, Latium, Rocca di Papa, Fig. 2; ♂ specimen from Spain, Cantabria, Campollo, Fig. 3), and of M. matronalis Audisio &amp; Spornraft (♂ specimen from Italy, Latium, Rocca di Papa, Fig. 4). Scale bar = 2.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173303/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
